cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CE

This paper presents a machine learning approach for modeling polypharmacy side effects using a multimodal graph of protein-protein interactions, drug-protein target interactions, and drug-drug interactions. The approach uses a graph convolutional neural network for multirelational link prediction in multimodal networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) due to the use of neural networks and graph modeling. The paper also involves data management and analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as potential sub-categories.
